#: {{ux|en|None of my '''siblings''' are married yet.}}
# {{lb|en|comptheory}} A [[node]] in a [[data structure]] that shares its [[parent]] with another node.
# {{lb|en|taxonomy}} The most closely related species, or one of several most closely species when none can be determined to be more closely related.
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=April 1, 1990|journal=Genetics|volume=124|issue=4|pages=909-920|author=P. Hutter et al.|title=A genetic basis for the inviability of hybrids between sibling species of Drosophila|url=https://www.genetics.org/content/124/4/909.short|passage=''D. simulans'', ''D. mauritiana'' and ''D. sechellia'' (which we will call “the '''siblings'''” when we do not need to distinguish among them) have homosequential polytene chromosome banding patterns differing from those of ''D. melanogaster'' by one long inversion on chromosome arm ''3R'' and a few much smaller inversions.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=November 26, 2015|doi=10.3897/zookeys.540.9791|journal=ZooKeys|volume=540|pages=211-237|author=Lucie Vaníčková et al.|title=Current knowledge of the species complex ''Anastrepha fraterculus'' (Diptera, Tephritidae) in Brazil|passage=Bush suggested that this difference might represent a case of chromosomal polymorphism or, more likely, '''sibling''' species.}}

